The ping statistics are reset to defaults when a ping is started, and updated when the ping stops. Dynamic pingTable information is used only once, for the next ping. Static pingTable information is used for all pings by default, whenever the respective dynamic settings are not specified.

pingSentPackets.name: pingSentPackets
pingSentPackets.description: The number of ping packets sent to the target in the last ping. The default before the completion of a ping is zero.

pingReceivedPackets.name: pingReceivedPackets
pingReceivedPackets.description: The number of packets received from the target in the last ping. The default before the completion of a ping is zero.

pingMinimumRoundTripTime.name: pingMinimumRoundTripTime
pingMinimumRoundTripTime.description: The quickest round trip time taken by any of the ping packets in milliseconds in the last ping. The default before the completion of a ping is negative one.

pingAverageRoundTripTime.name: pingAverageRoundTripTime
pingAverageRoundTripTime.description: The average round trip time taken by the ping packets in milliseconds in the last ping. The default before the completion of a ping is zero.

pingMaximumRoundTripTime.name: pingMaximumRoundTripTime
pingMaximumRoundTripTime.description: The slowest round trip time taken by any of the ping packets in milliseconds in the last ping. The default before the completion of a ping is zero.

pingTrap.name: pingTrap
pingTrap.description: A ping trap is generated when a ping has completed. Traps are only generated if the variable pingTrapOnCompletion is set to true(1) in the dynamic ping entry. A trap is still generated if the ping is stopped prematurely by setting the variable pingStatus to stop/stopped(2).

dhcpRangeEntry.name: dhcpRangeEntry
dhcpRangeEntry.description: A single entry of the DHCP range table. This contains information about a single DHCP range configured on this device.

dhcpRangeIndex.name: dhcpRangeIndex
dhcpRangeIndex.description: The index of this DHCP range. DHCP ranges are stored in a list which is ordered by range name. The index gives the place in the list. Note that if ranges are added or deleted, the index for a given range will change. Since this table is read-only, this will not have an undue effect, but if in future this table is made read-write, a mechanism will have to be created to lock the indices of the range table while SET operations are proceeding.

dhcpRangeName.name: dhcpRangeName
dhcpRangeName.description: The name given to identify this DHCP range. This is the ultimate method for uniquely identifying this range. Names are compared without regard to case, for example >range1< will be treated as the same as >RANGE1<.

dhcpRangeBaseAddress.name: dhcpRangeBaseAddress
dhcpRangeBaseAddress.description: The base address of this range. This address defines the lower bound of the range of IP addresses which can be allocated to devices requesting an IP address via DHCP.

dhcpRangeNumberOfAddresses.name: dhcpRangeNumberOfAddresses
dhcpRangeNumberOfAddresses.description: The number of IP address in this range. This number defines the upper bound of the range of IP addresses which can be allocated to devices requesting an IP address via DHCP.

dhcpRangeGateway.name: dhcpRangeGateway
dhcpRangeGateway.description: The IP address of the BOOTP relay agent which will be relaying DHCP requests for this range. If this address is 0.0.0.0, then there will be no BOOTP relay agent and the range will be allocated to devices directly connected to this device.

dhcpRangeExhaustedGateway.name: dhcpRangeExhaustedGateway
dhcpRangeExhaustedGateway.description: Whenever a DHCP client attempts to lease an IP address and the DHCP server cannot provide an address, this variable is set to the gateway address of the DHCP request. The gateway address is the IP address of the gateway acting as a BOOTP relay agent for the request. If there is no gateway, the address will be 0.0.0.0. If the gateway address is non-zero, the DHCP range from which the allocation should have been made will able to be identified by lookup in the DHCP range table.

dhcpRangeExhaustedInterface.name: dhcpRangeExhaustedInterface
dhcpRangeExhaustedInterface.description: Whenever a DHCP client attempts to lease an IP address and the DHCP server cannot provide an address, this variable is set to the IP address of the interface which received the DHCP request. If the gateway address associated with the failed DHCP request is 0.0.0.0, the interface address will be able to be used to lookup the range that was exhausted and from which the allocation should have been made.

dhcpRangeExhaustedTrap.name: dhcpRangeExhaustedTrap
dhcpRangeExhaustedTrap.description: This trap is generated when a DHCP client makes a request for an IP address and the request cannot be satisfied because all addresses in the range are already allocated to other devices.

dhcpClientTable.name: dhcpClientTable
dhcpClientTable.description: The table of defined DHCP range client addresses.

dhcpClientEntry.name: dhcpClientEntry
dhcpClientEntry.description: A single entry of the DHCP range client table. This contains information about a single DHCP range client address.

dhcpClientIpAddress.name: dhcpClientIpAddress
dhcpClientIpAddress.description: An IP address from the range of available addresses.

dhcpClientID.name: dhcpClientID
dhcpClientID.description: The hardware address of the client, if any, that has been assigned the IP address.

dhcpClientState.name: dhcpClientState
dhcpClientState.description: The state of the IP address; one of unused, inuse or reclaim.

dhcpClientType.name: dhcpClientType
dhcpClientType.description: The type of allocation mechanism applied to the IP address; one of static, auto or dyn.

dhcpClientExpiry.name: dhcpClientExpiry
dhcpClientExpiry.description: The expiry date for dynamically allocated IP address.

firewallTrapMessage.name: firewallTrapMessage
firewallTrapMessage.description: The last message sent in a firewall TRAP. This variable is really just a placeholder for the object sent in the firewall TRAP, but can be read independently if required. Note however that a new TRAP will cause this variable to be overwritten.

firewallTrap.name: firewallTrap
firewallTrap.description: A firewall trap is generated when the firewall detects an intrusion or attack and notifies the router manager. Firewall trap notifications are enabled with the command ENABLE FIREWALL NOTIFY=SNMP.

swiPortEntry.name: swiPortEntry
swiPortEntry.description: An entry in the port information table.

swiPortNumber.name: swiPortNumber
swiPortNumber.description: This object identifies the port of the switch.

swiPortIngressLimit.name: swiPortIngressLimit
swiPortIngressLimit.description: The Ingress Bandwidth Limit applied to the port. A value of zero indicates that no limit is set.

swiPortEgressLimit.name: swiPortEgressLimit
swiPortEgressLimit.description: The Egress Bandwidth Limit applied to the port. A value of zero indicates that no limit is set.

swi56xxPortCounterTable.name: swi56xxPortCounterTable
swi56xxPortCounterTable.description: Table of swi56xx port counter properties.

swi56xxPortCounterEntry.name: swi56xxPortCounterEntry
swi56xxPortCounterEntry.description: An entry in the port information table.

swi56xxPortNumber.name: swi56xxPortNumber
swi56xxPortNumber.description: This object identifies the port of the switch.

swi56xxRxTx64kPkts.name: swi56xxRxTx64kPkts
swi56xxRxTx64kPkts.description: The number of 64kB packets received and transmitted.

swi56xxRxTx65To127kPkts.name: swi56xxRxTx65To127kPkts
swi56xxRxTx65To127kPkts.description: The number of 65kB To 127kB packets received and transmitted.

swi56xxRxTx128To255kPkts.name: swi56xxRxTx128To255kPkts
swi56xxRxTx128To255kPkts.description: The number of 128kB To 255kB packets received and transmitted.

swi56xxRxTx256To511kPkts.name: swi56xxRxTx256To511kPkts
swi56xxRxTx256To511kPkts.description: The number of 256kB To 511kB packets received and transmitted.

swi56xxRxTx512To1023kPkts.name: swi56xxRxTx512To1023kPkts
swi56xxRxTx512To1023kPkts.description: The number of 512kB To 1023kB packets received and transmitted.

swi56xxRxTx1024ToMaxPktSzPkts.name: swi56xxRxTx1024ToMaxPktSzPkts
swi56xxRxTx1024ToMaxPktSzPkts.description: The number of 1024kB To MaxPktSz packets received and transmitted.

swi56xxRxTx519To1522kPkts.name: swi56xxRxTx519To1522kPkts
swi56xxRxTx519To1522kPkts.description: The number of 519kB To 1522kB packets received and transmitted.

swi56xxPortRxFCSErrors.name: swi56xxPortRxFCSErrors
swi56xxPortRxFCSErrors.description: The number of frames received containing a Frame Check Sequence error.

swi56xxPortRxMulticastPkts.name: swi56xxPortRxMulticastPkts
swi56xxPortRxMulticastPkts.description: The number of multicast packets received.

swi56xxPortRxBroadcastPkts.name: swi56xxPortRxBroadcastPkts
swi56xxPortRxBroadcastPkts.description: The number of broadcast packets received.

swi56xxPortRxPauseMACCtlFrms.name: swi56xxPortRxPauseMACCtlFrms
swi56xxPortRxPauseMACCtlFrms.description: The number of valid PAUSE MAC Control frames received.

swi56xxPortRxOversizePkts.name: swi56xxPortRxOversizePkts
swi56xxPortRxOversizePkts.description: The number of oversize packets received.

swi56xxPortRxJabbers.name: swi56xxPortRxJabbers
swi56xxPortRxJabbers.description: The number of jabber frames received.

swi56xxPortRxMACControlFrms.name: swi56xxPortRxMACControlFrms
swi56xxPortRxMACControlFrms.description: The number of MAC Control frames (Pause and Unsupported) received.

swi56xxPortRxUnsupportOpcode.name: swi56xxPortRxUnsupportOpcode
swi56xxPortRxUnsupportOpcode.description: The number of MAC Control frames with unsupported opcode (i.e. not Pause) received.

swi56xxPortRxAlignmentErrors.name: swi56xxPortRxAlignmentErrors
swi56xxPortRxAlignmentErrors.description: The number of frames with alignment errors received.

swi56xxPortRxOutOfRngeLenFld.name: swi56xxPortRxOutOfRngeLenFld
swi56xxPortRxOutOfRngeLenFld.description: The number of packets with length out of range received.

swi56xxPortRxSymErDurCarrier.name: swi56xxPortRxSymErDurCarrier
swi56xxPortRxSymErDurCarrier.description: The number of frames with invalid data symbols received.

swi56xxPortRxCarrierSenseErr.name: swi56xxPortRxCarrierSenseErr
swi56xxPortRxCarrierSenseErr.description: The number of false carrier conditions between frames received.

swi56xxPortRxUndersizePkts.name: swi56xxPortRxUndersizePkts
swi56xxPortRxUndersizePkts.description: The number of undersized packets received.

swi56xxPortTxFCSErrors.name: swi56xxPortTxFCSErrors
swi56xxPortTxFCSErrors.description: The number of frames containing a Frame Check Sequence error transmitted.

swi56xxPortTxMulticastPkts.name: swi56xxPortTxMulticastPkts
swi56xxPortTxMulticastPkts.description: The number of multicast packets transmitted.

swi56xxPortTxBroadcastPkts.name: swi56xxPortTxBroadcastPkts
swi56xxPortTxBroadcastPkts.description: The number of broadcast packets transmitted.

swi56xxPortTxPauseMACCtlFrms.name: swi56xxPortTxPauseMACCtlFrms
swi56xxPortTxPauseMACCtlFrms.description: The number of valid PAUSE MAC Control frames transmitted.

swi56xxPortTxOversizePkts.name: swi56xxPortTxOversizePkts
swi56xxPortTxOversizePkts.description: The number of oversize packets transmitted.

swi56xxPortTxJabbers.name: swi56xxPortTxJabbers
swi56xxPortTxJabbers.description: The number of jabber frames transmitted.

swi56xxPortTxPauseCtrlFrms.name: swi56xxPortTxPauseCtrlFrms
swi56xxPortTxPauseCtrlFrms.description: The number of Pause control frames transmitted.

swi56xxPortTxFrameWDeferrdTx.name: swi56xxPortTxFrameWDeferrdTx
swi56xxPortTxFrameWDeferrdTx.description: The number of frames deferred once before successful transmission.

swi56xxPortTxFrmWExcesDefer.name: swi56xxPortTxFrmWExcesDefer
swi56xxPortTxFrmWExcesDefer.description: The number of frame aborted after too many deferrals.

swi56xxPortTxSingleCollsnFrm.name: swi56xxPortTxSingleCollsnFrm
swi56xxPortTxSingleCollsnFrm.description: The number of frames which experienced exactly one collision.

swi56xxPortTxMultCollsnFrm.name: swi56xxPortTxMultCollsnFrm
swi56xxPortTxMultCollsnFrm.description: The number of frames which experienced 2 to 15 collisions (including late collisions).

swi56xxPortTxLateCollsns.name: swi56xxPortTxLateCollsns
swi56xxPortTxLateCollsns.description: The number of frames which experienced late collisions.

swi56xxPortTxExcessivCollsns.name: swi56xxPortTxExcessivCollsns
swi56xxPortTxExcessivCollsns.description: The number of frames aborted before transmission after 16 collisions.

swi56xxPortMiscDropEvents.name: swi56xxPortMiscDropEvents
swi56xxPortMiscDropEvents.description: The number of packets discarded at ingress port.

swi56xxPortMiscTaggedPktTx.name: swi56xxPortMiscTaggedPktTx
swi56xxPortMiscTaggedPktTx.description: The number of VLAN tagged packets transmitted.

swi56xxPortMiscTotalPktTxAbort.name: swi56xxPortMiscTotalPktTxAbort
swi56xxPortMiscTotalPktTxAbort.description: The number of Layer 2 and 3 packets aborted during transmission.

swi56xxPortHWMultiTTLexpired.name: swi56xxPortHWMultiTTLexpired
swi56xxPortHWMultiTTLexpired.description: Number of multicast TTL expired frames.

swi56xxPortHWMultiRxDrops.name: swi56xxPortHWMultiRxDrops
swi56xxPortHWMultiRxDrops.description: Number of multicast frames dropped at reception

swi56xxPortHWMultiTxDrops.name: swi56xxPortHWMultiTxDrops
swi56xxPortHWMultiTxDrops.description: NNumber of multicast frames dropped at transmission

swiDebugMemoryParityErrors.name: swiDebugMemoryParityErrors
swiDebugMemoryParityErrors.description: For switches based on certain switch chips, the number of parity errors that have been detected in packet memory associated with the switch. If the device does not include the counting of memory parity errors, this variable will return 0.

swiIntrusionDetectionTrap.name: swiIntrusionDetectionTrap
swiIntrusionDetectionTrap.description: An intrusion detection trap is generated when a port has intrusion detection enabled, and the action taken when intrusion is detected is to generate a trap. Intrusion is detected when the number of MAC addresses learned on the port exceeds the configured learn limit. The ifIndex of the port is included in the trap.

lbShowGlobalTable.name: lbShowGlobalTable
lbShowGlobalTable.description: General configuration and status of all of the virtual balancers configured on the router.

lbShowGlobalEntry.name: lbShowGlobalEntry
lbShowGlobalEntry.description: An entry in the global table.

lbGlobalIndex.name: lbGlobalIndex
lbGlobalIndex.description: The index for the global table.

lbAffinityTimeOut.name: lbAffinityTimeOut
lbAffinityTimeOut.description: The length of time in seconds that a resource can be associated to a source IP address or Cookie after the connection has been closed.

lbOrphanTimeOut.name: lbOrphanTimeOut
lbOrphanTimeOut.description: The length of time in seconds that a connection can exist without having any data traversing it, before being declared an orphan and closed by the router.

lbCriticalRst.name: lbCriticalRst
lbCriticalRst.description: The ratio of total messages received from a resource that can be TCP RST messages represented as a percentage.

lbTotalResources.name: lbTotalResources
lbTotalResources.description: The total number of resources configured on the router.

lbTotalResPools.name: lbTotalResPools
lbTotalResPools.description: The total number of resource pools configured on the router.

lbTotalVirtBals.name: lbTotalVirtBals
lbTotalVirtBals.description: The total number of virtual balancers configured on the router.

lbCurrentConnections.name: lbCurrentConnections
lbCurrentConnections.description: Displays the current total number of connections to all resources in every resource pool on the router.

lbShowResTable.name: lbShowResTable
lbShowResTable.description: A list about the general information about for a given resource.

lbShowResEntry.name: lbShowResEntry
lbShowResEntry.description: An entry in the resource table.

lbResIndex.name: lbResIndex
lbResIndex.description: The index for the resource table.

lbResIp.name: lbResIp
lbResIp.description: The IP address that a virtual balancer uses to accesses the resource.

lbResPort.name: lbResPort
lbResPort.description: The port that the service that the resource offer is accessed on.

lbResState.name: lbResState
lbResState.description: The current state of the resource, either UP, DOWN, or CLOSING.

lbResWeight.name: lbResWeight
lbResWeight.description: The weight that the virtual balancer will apply to the resource when selecting resources to try a connection to from a resource pool using either the WEIGHTEDLEASTCONNECT or WEIGHTEDLOTTERY selection algorithms.

lbResTotalConnections.name: lbResTotalConnections
lbResTotalConnections.description: The total number of successful connections that have been made to this resource while it has been in the UP state.

lbResCurrentConnections.name: lbResCurrentConnections
lbResCurrentConnections.description: The total number of connections currently made to the resource.

lbShowResPoolTable.name: lbShowResPoolTable
lbShowResPoolTable.description: A list about the general information about for a given resource pool.

lbShowResPoolEntry.name: lbShowResPoolEntry
lbShowResPoolEntry.description: An entry in the resource pool table.

lbResPoolIndex.name: lbResPoolIndex
lbResPoolIndex.description: The index for the resource pool table.

lbResPoolResourceIndex.name: lbResPoolResourceIndex
